  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "Mr. Yang's old file included a photograph of him standing proudly by the library door.",
      "zh": "楊先生的舊資料裡有一張他驕傲地站在圖書館門口的照片。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"He looked honest and kind,\" Coco said, \"even in an old black-and-white picture.\"",
      "zh": "Coco 說：「就算是舊的黑白照片，他看起來也很誠實善良。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "She felt a small ache in her heart, thinking about how deeply someone could care without ever being thanked.",
      "zh": "她心裡有一點酸酸的感覺，想到一個人可以這麼深地在乎，卻從來沒有被好好感謝過。"
    },
    {
      "en": "That night, Coco couldn't stop thinking about a small metal box working alone in a closed, forgotten room.",
      "zh": "那天晚上，Coco 一直忘不了那個獨自在一間關著、被遺忘的房間裡運作的小金屬盒子。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"We can't just leave it like this,\" she told Bernice the next morning. \"But we can't just tell everyone, either.\"",
      "zh": "隔天早上她跟 Bernice 說：「我們不能就這樣放著不管，但我們也不能直接告訴所有人。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "They brought the whole story to Mr. Pan, from the closed door to Mr. Yang's name in the old papers.",
      "zh": "他們把整件事從那扇關著的門到舊資料裡楊先生的名字，全部告訴了潘老師。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mr. Pan was quiet for a long moment before he spoke.",
      "zh": "潘老師沉默了好一會兒才開口。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"You found a case,\" he said. \"But this time, the case isn't really a problem to solve.\"",
      "zh": "他說：「你們找到了一個案子，但這次，這個案子其實不是一個需要解決的問題。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"So what do we do with it?\" Bernice asked.",
      "zh": "Bernice 問：「那我們該拿它怎麼辦？」"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"You tell the story,\" Mr. Pan said. \"Just not as a mystery. As a thank-you.\"",
      "zh": "潘老師說：「把這個故事說出來，不是當成一個謎團，而是當成一句謝謝。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "For their next episode, Coco and Bernice did not talk about clues, keys, or closed doors.",
      "zh": "在下一集裡，Coco 和 Bernice 沒有提到線索、鑰匙，或關著的門。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Instead, they talked about a night worker named Mr. Yang, who once made sure no student had to study in the dark.",
      "zh": "他們談的是一位叫楊先生的夜間工友，他曾經確保沒有任何學生要在黑暗中唸書。"
    },
    {
      "en": "They talked about a small machine that had quietly kept doing his job for eight years after he was gone.",
      "zh": "他們也談到一台小機器，在他離開之後，默默替他做了八年的工作。"
    },
    {
      "en": "When the episode played in class, the room was completely silent until it ended.",
      "zh": "這一集在班上播放的時候，教室裡一片安靜，直到播完為止。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Then someone asked a simple question: \"Can we still turn the light on for him?\"",
      "zh": "接著有人問了一個簡單的問題：「我們還可以繼續為他把燈點亮嗎？」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mr. Pan brought the idea to the school office, and this time nobody argued.",
      "zh": "潘老師把這個想法帶去學校辦公室，這次沒有人反對。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The old library stayed full of boxes, but the timer was allowed to keep its small job.",
      "zh": "舊圖書館還是繼續拿來放東西，但那個計時器被允許繼續做它的小工作。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Every night, at exactly nine fifteen, the light still turns on, and now everyone knows why.",
      "zh": "每天晚上九點十五分，那盞燈依然會亮起，而現在大家都知道原因了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Coco added a short line to her notebook: some cases don't end with an answer. They end with a decision.",
      "zh": "Coco 在筆記本上加了一行短短的字：有些案子的結局不是一個答案，而是一個決定。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice, for once, agreed completely. \"That's going in the show,\" she said. \"Word for word.\"",
      "zh": "這一次，Bernice 完全同意：「這句話要放進節目裡，」她說：「一字不改。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "A week later, the Friday Box received a note that made both of them laugh out loud.",
      "zh": "一星期後，Friday Box 收到了一張讓他們兩個都笑出聲來的紙條。"
    },
    {
      "en": "It read: \"The vending machine by the gym never runs out of my favorite drink. Even when it should be empty. Is someone helping me, or is something weird going on?\"",
      "zh": "紙條上寫著：「體育館旁邊的自動販賣機，永遠不會賣完我最喜歡的那款飲料，就算應該早就賣完了也一樣。是有人在幫我，還是有什麼奇怪的事在發生？」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice smiled right away. \"Finally,\" she said. \"A case with snacks.\"",
      "zh": "Bernice 立刻笑了：「終於，」她說：「一個跟零食有關的案子。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Coco couldn't help smiling too. \"Let's find out,\" she said, already reaching for her notebook.",
      "zh": "Coco 也忍不住笑了：「我們來查清楚吧。」她已經伸手去拿她的筆記本。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Whatever the truth was this time, one thing was already clear: their little podcast had turned into something the whole school was starting to trust.",
      "zh": "不管這次的真相是什麼，有一件事已經很清楚：他們的小 podcast，漸漸變成了全校開始信任的東西。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mr. Tan mentioned once that Mr. Yang used to bring him hot tea and homemade cookies during long winter nights of work.",
      "zh": "陳先生曾提過，楊先生以前在漫長的冬夜工作時，總會帶熱茶和自製餅乾給他。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mr. Tan kept a small toolbox with a hammer, a knife, tape, and spare parts for exactly this kind of quiet, patient repair.",
      "zh": "陳先生有一個小工具箱，裡面放著鎚子、刀子、膠帶，還有備用零件，專門用來做這種安靜又有耐心的修理工作。"
    }
  ],
